:::summary
Clive Staples Lewis (1898–1963) was a British author, Oxford don, and one of the most influential Christian writers of the 20th century. A former atheist who was converted to Christianity in part through conversations with J.R.R. Tolkien, Lewis became a brilliant defender of rational Christian faith. His works — from *Mere Christianity* to *The Chronicles of Narnia* — have profoundly influenced millions of readers, including many Latter-day Saints.
:::

